# Project Structure Guidelines

## Directory Structure
```
src/
├── assets/           # Static assets (images, fonts, etc.)
├── components/       # Reusable components
│   ├── common/      # Shared components (buttons, inputs, etc.)
│   ├── layout/      # Layout components (header, footer, etc.)
│   └── features/    # Feature-specific components
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
├── pages/           # Page components
├── services/        # API services and external integrations
├── store/           # State management (Redux/Context)
├── styles/          # Global styles and theme
├── utils/           # Utility functions and helpers
└── constants/       # Application constants
```

## Key Files
- [src/App.js](mdc:src/App.js) - Main application component
- [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js) - Application entry point
- [src/store/index.js](mdc:src/store/index.js) - State management setup
- [src/services/api.js](mdc:src/services/api.js) - API configuration

## Best Practices
1. Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility
2. Use feature-based organization for complex features
3. Maintain clear separation between UI components and business logic
4. Follow consistent naming conventions:
   - Components: PascalCase (e.g., `OrderForm.js`)
   - Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatPrice.js`)
   - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
